{
  "stem": "628.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she stood up in the bed, and she looked at all of us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then she fall down, and she was gone.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When they took out of the house, my grandmother wanted throw herself out of the window, when they took the-- the-- how do you call it, the--",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, the coffin, out of-- she looked through the windowm and she went my Lotti, my Lotti.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was already the first, what's it called, hit, which hit us strong in our family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Definitely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They also stopped schools then-- soon after that, Jewish schools.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, because they hated the Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, under Hitler's-- beginning, '33, later, when he became in power officially, then he was already strongly in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But, before that, the voting and the SR and the SS went with him, it was going on all the time when I was the child.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a matter of fact, where we were living, our neighbors, some of them were very anti-Semitically.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they didn't like us, but they didn't show it before Hitler was voted in '39, before the war started, '38.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then they became more, what's it called, more obvious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But, anyhow, she was buried, in Weissensee.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She got a grave there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We went together there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after-- soon after that, in '36, I remember that a lot of people immigrated because they felt that Hitler is coming, and there's nothing to stop that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So my mother, being stateless, she married my father who was Polish, she had to leave Germany in '36, and leave us children behind-- the two of us now.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She went to England, to London.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had to work in the housework.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
